  <summary>7/24/2000--Introduced.
Medikid Health Care Expansion Act of 2000 - Amends titles XIX (Medicaid) and XXI (Children's Health Insurance) to provide for: (1) increased access of children to health care insurance, including those from higher income families; and (2) optional State coverage of low-income, uninsured pregnant women.Amends the Public Health Service Act to extend the authorization of graduate medical education funding for children's hospitals.</summary>
